Convolvulus ensifolius P.P.A.Ferreira &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Simão-Bianchini">Simao-Bianchini</normalizedToken>
, Phytotaxa 135: 29. 2013. (Ferreira et al. 2013: 29).
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
BRAZIL, Rio Grande do Sul, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. P.A. Ferreira 300</emphasis>
(holotype ICN; isotypes K!, SP).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
Prostrate perennial with woody base, the stems winged, twining at the apices. Leaves shortly petiolate, 2-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.4 cm, linear-oblong, base sagittate, apex acute, glabrous; petiole 2-6 mm. Flowers solitary; peduncles 25-60 mm, shortly winged; bracteoles 3-5 nn, lanceolate, deciduous; pedicels 8-12 mm; outer sepals 6-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, obovate, truncate, mucronulate, glabrous or canescent, the margins ciliolate; inner sepals similar but with scarious margins; corolla 1.8-2.2 cm long, white, glabrous, midpetaline bands sericeous; ovary glabrous, subglobose; style divided 6-9 mm above base; stigmas 3-4 mm. Capsule glabrous, apiculate; seeds black, glabrous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
Brazil (Rio Grande do Sul, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraná">Parana</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
Resembling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O'Donell, Lilloa 29: 293. 1959. (O'Donell" authorityYear="1959" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lilloi" order="Solanales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lilloi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Convolvulus lilloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O'Donell, Lilloa 23: 430. 1950. (O'Donell" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Chodat" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hasslerianus" order="Solanales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hasslerianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Convolvulus hasslerianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the solitary flowers and shortly petiolate leaves but near glabrous, the leaves linear-oblong and the sepals much shorter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
